<section class="faq-section" id="faq">
  <div class="faq-inner">
    <div class="faq-left fade-up">
      <h2>We're here<br>to help.</h2>
      <p>Can't find your answer? Email us at info@dayguard.com. We'll reply shortly.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-right">

      <p class="faq-category">How It Works</p>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          How does day–guard work?
          <span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none"><line x1="5" y1="0" x2="5" y2="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="10" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>day–guard combines clinically backed ingredients that help your body break down acetaldehyde (a toxic alcohol byproduct), replenish key nutrients, and reduce inflammation.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What are the key ingredients?
          <span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none"><line x1="5" y1="0" x2="5" y2="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="10" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>day–guard features four functional areas: liver support (DHM, milk thistle, turmeric, L-cysteine), electrolytes (magnesium, sodium), vitamins (B1, B2, B3, B6), and gut health (pear, ginger, xylitol, prebiotics).</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          How is it different from electrolytes?
          <span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none"><line x1="5" y1="0" x2="5" y2="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="10" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>While electrolytes address hydration, day–guard goes beyond simple rehydration. It also supports your body's natural detox process, replenishes lost nutrients, and protects your liver and gut health.</p></div>
      </div>

      <p class="faq-category">Usage</p>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          When do I take it?
          <span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none"><line x1="5" y1="0" x2="5" y2="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="10" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Take one stick right before or during drinking and another for every 3–5 drinks.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Can I have multiple in one night?
          <span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none"><line x1="5" y1="0" x2="5" y2="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="10" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Most people take one before drinking and, optionally, another for every 3–5 drinks. All ingredients are within safe daily limits.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Do I need to mix it with anything?
          <span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none"><line x1="5" y1="0" x2="5" y2="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="10" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. Each stick is a ready–to–eat jelly — no water or mixing required.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Can I take it without alcohol?
          <span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none"><line x1="5" y1="0" x2="5" y2="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="10" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Many people use day–guard for general liver, gut, and nutrient support — even on days they don't drink.</p></div>
      </div>

      <p class="faq-category">Safety &amp; Manufacturing</p>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Is it FDA approved / safe?
          <span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none"><line x1="5" y1="0" x2="5" y2="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="10" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Like all dietary supplements, day–guard is not FDA–approved to treat or prevent disease, but is manufactured in FDA–registered, GMP–certified facilities.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Where is it made?
          <span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none"><line x1="5" y1="0" x2="5" y2="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="10" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>day–guard is made in Korea by a pharmaceutical partner founded in 1963, bringing over 60 years of clinical expertise.</p></div>
      </div>

      <p class="faq-category">Effectiveness</p>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Does it help with hangovers?
          <span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none"><line x1="5" y1="0" x2="5" y2="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="10" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>day–guard provides complete support for your body when you drink, helping you feel clearer and more refreshed the next day through supporting liver and gut function.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Does it prevent intoxication?
          <span class="faq-chevron"><svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none"><line x1="5" y1="0" x2="5" y2="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="10" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. day–guard will not prevent intoxication or enhance sobriety. It simply supports your body's natural detox and recovery process.</p></div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

